cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
1) cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper focuses on community detection in networks, which is a subfield of social and information networks. 
2) cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new algorithm for community detection and provides theoretical analysis of its performance, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
3) cs.LG (Machine Learning) - Community detection can be seen as a type of unsupervised learning problem, which is a subfield of machine learning. 
4) cs.SD (Software Engineering) - The paper may also fall under the scope of software engineering as it proposes a new approach for community detection. 
5) cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may also fall under the scope of systems and control as it deals with analyzing the performance of a system (the HICODE algorithm) in detecting hidden communities in networks.
